There are two ways to fix this:

Option A — Add a Sign Up flow in the app The login screen gets a toggle: "Sign In / Sign Up". You type email + password, it creates the account. Anyone with the link can register though, so you'd want to add an invite code or email whitelist to control who can join.

Option B — Admin-only user management (recommended for a farm) You stay the only admin. Inside the app, you get a simple "Users" section where you can type an email and send them an invite link directly from Supabase Auth — no one can self-register.

Option C — Hardcode allowed emails A simple list of approved emails in your .env. Anyone not on the list gets rejected even if they try to sign up.

For a farm tracker where you know exactly who should have access, Option A with an invite code is probably the cleanest — you share the code with your team, they sign up themselves, strangers can't get in.

